<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TT1.3">
<l>vākai virintuveṇ ṇeṟṟo lippa mayaṅkiruḷ kūrnaṭu nāḷai yāṅkē</l>
<l>kūkaiyo ṭāṇṭalai pāṭa vāntai kōṭataṉ mēṟkutit tōṭa vīci</l>
<l>yīkai paṭartoṭar kaḷḷi nīḻa līma miṭucuṭu kāṭṭa kattē</l>
<l>yākaṅ kuḷirntaṉa lāṭu meṅka ḷappa ṉiṭantiru vālaṅ kāṭē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The place of our father who dances with fire, [his] chest cooling,</l>
<l>while Sirissa expands [and its] white seed-pods sound, there at midnight</l>
<l>when opaque darkness abounds, while man-headed ones sing along with owls,</l>
<l>while spotted owlets hop on that which has branches [and] run, within the cremation</l>
<l>ground that burns when [they] place pyres in the shade of Euphorbia spreading</l>
<l>[and] linking in scattering with mimosa, is Tiruvalaṅkāṭu.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
